Sentencas: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+delta (LSCO4) material with K2NiF4-type structure has been synthesized via a citric-nitrate process and characterized.
Titulo: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+δ-CGO composite as cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Composite materials La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+delta-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta (CGO) (LSCO4-CGO) have been prepared and evaluated as cathode for intermediate temperature SOFC (IT-SOFC) based on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolytes.
Titulo: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+δ-CGO composite as cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LSCO4 oxide is chemically compatible with CGO and LSGM electrolyte at temperature up to 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+δ-CGO composite as cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with the pure LSCO4, the optimum composition of LSCO4-35 wt % CGO exhibits better electrochemical activity for oxygen reduction.
Titulo: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+δ-CGO composite as cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Also, for LSCO4-35 wt % CGO electrode, SEM results suggest that better microstructure is obtained and the electrode forms good contact with the electrolyte after sintering at 1000 degrees C for 2 h. At 750 degrees C, the polarization resistance of the LSCO4-35 wt % CGO composite cathode is about 0.21 Omega cm(2) in air.
Titulo: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+δ-CGO composite as cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A cell with a 1.2 mm thick LSGM electrolyte, NiO as anode, and LSCO4-35 wt % CGO as cathode displays a maximum power density of 515 mW cm(-2) at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+δ-CGO composite as cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that LSCO4-CGO composite materials are promising cathode candidates for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with LSGM electrolyte.
Titulo: La0.8Sr1.2CoO4+δ-CGO composite as cathode on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-δ electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
